                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This inscription is dated in the ninth year of <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Rājendra-Choḷa-deva</hi>. It records the gift of a piece of land from the great assembly (<hi rend="italic">mahāsabhā</hi>) of <hi rend="bold">Śi[ṟi]davūr</hi>, <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Narasiṁha-maṅgalam</hi> to “our lord of <hi rend="bold">Tirukkaḍalmallai</hi>.” By this the Shore Temple at <hi rend="bold">Māmallapuram</hi> seems to be meant.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
